% --- ABSTRACT ---
\begin{abstract}
\noindent High failure rates in reforestation projects are often due to a mismatch between species and local site conditions, a problem exacerbated in remote, offline environments. We address how an on-device, multimodal AI can provide real-time ecological analysis. We present TerraSeed, a system using the Gemma 3n model to synthesize visual (soil imagery) and auditory (soundscape) data. It generates actionable planting plans without needing cloud connectivity, ensuring privacy and utility. A case study demonstrates the system's ability to produce a detailed, scientifically-grounded plan from real-world inputs, showing the viability of this offline-first approach.
\end{abstract}

% --- SECTION 1: INTRODUCTION ---
\section{Introduction}
The success of global reforestation efforts hinges on sapling survival, which is often compromised by a mismatch between the species planted and the site's specific micro-environment. While remote sensing provides macro-level data, field workers lack tools for immediate, granular analysis of soil and local conditions at the point of planting. This creates a critical gap between ecological knowledge and practical action.

This paper introduces TerraSeed, an AI-powered field guide designed to fill this gap. Operating entirely on-device, it leverages the Gemma 3n model to analyze environmental inputs and generate immediate planting recommendations. We detail its methodology, which synthesizes visual and acoustic data, present a case study demonstrating its output, and discuss the implications of a private, offline-first approach to ecological AI.

% --- SECTION 2: SYSTEM AND METHODOLOGY ---
\section{System and Methodology}
TerraSeed is designed as an offline-first mobile application. The architecture consists of a simple user interface for capturing image and audio inputs, which are then passed directly to the on-device Gemma 3n model. All processing occurs locally, ensuring user privacy and functionality without an internet connection.

The core of the system is a prompt-driven methodology for \textbf{Holistic Ecosystem Assessment}. This structured process guides the AI through four steps:
\begin{enumerate}
    \setlength\itemsep{-0.5em} % Reduce space between list items
    \item \textbf{Visual Analysis:} Identify soil type, plant species, or signs of stress from the input image.
    \item \textbf{Acoustic Analysis:} Identify bioacoustic signals and environmental sounds from the audio recording.
    \item \textbf{Synthesis \& Correlation:} Find causal links between the visual and auditory data (e.g., does the sound of wind explain the sight of a wilting leaf?). This is the key step for an accurate diagnosis.
    \item \textbf{Diagnosis \& Recommendation:} Based on the synthesized understanding, generate a single, actionable planting or maintenance plan.
\end{enumerate}

